Here are some software testing best practices and a test to review. Produce a list of test issues according to these practices, including the bullet and number of each practice. You main add your own review tips in a dedicated section

A. 1. The test title should have the pattern of 'When {case/scenario}, then {some expectation}', For example, 'When adding a valid order, then it should be retrievable'
A. 2. Each data or assumption in the assertion phase, must appear in the arrange phase in the beginning of the test to make the result and cause clear to the reader
B. 1. Ensure the tests have a line break between the common phases: arrange, act and assert
C.17 There should be no redundant assertions
D.11 Details that are not direclty related with understanding the test result, should not be part of the test
